The film is available to watch on Disney+, and critics have included it among the top recommendations for films to watch this week.

name: Nguyen Phu Trong
summary: The death of Nguyen Phu Trong, the long-serving leader of Vietnam's Communist Party, has garnered significant attention. State media sources have confirmed Trong's passing at age 80, describing him as a symbol of Vietnamese authoritarianism. Trong's demise has left the country's succession plans uncertain, as he was the most powerful leader in the country. His legacy is marked by both his role in expanding Vietnam's international relations and his crackdowns on dissent. The U.S. Ambassador to Vietnam has issued a statement expressing condolences on Trong's passing, while international news outlets have highlighted his impact on Vietnamese politics and society.

name: Bella Hadid
summary: Adidas has removed Bella Hadid from a promotional campaign after criticism from the Israeli government over her support for Palestine. The controversy stemmed from Hadid's use in an ad for a sneaker inspired by the 1972 Munich Olympics, where Palestinian terrorists killed 11 Israeli athletes. Following the backlash, Adidas apologized and removed Hadid from the campaign. Meanwhile, Hadid has made headlines for her fashion choices, including a look reminiscent of the character Rory Gilmore, and her endorsement of the "girlhood" trend. She has also launched her own fragrance brand, Ôrebella.
